text.tspan: SARS-CoV-2 variants in analyzed sequences, France, May 11, 2020 to Feb
The number of analyzed sequences in the preceding two weeks that correspond to each variant group. This number may not
reflect the complete breakdown of cases since only a fraction of all cases are sequenced.
Source: GISAID, via CoVariants.org Last updated 12 March 2023
Note: Recently-discovered or actively-monitored variants may be overrepresented, as suspected cases of these variants are likely to be
sequenced preferentially or faster than other cases.
